Introduction

Base URL: http://surukori.top 
This documentation aims to provide all the information you need to work with our API.

<aside>As you scroll, you'll see code examples for working with the API in different programming languages in the dark area to the right (or as part of the content on mobile).
You can switch the language used with the tabs at the top right (or from the nav menu at the top left on mobile).</aside>

Authenticating requests

To authenticate requests, include a Authorization header with the value "{YOUR_SANCTUM_TOKEN}".

All authenticated endpoints are marked with a requires authentication badge in the documentation below.

Use a Sanctum token like: Bearer your_token_here

Endpoints

POST api/googlehandle

requires authentication

Example request:
curl --request POST \
    "http://surukori.top/api/googlehandle" \
    --header "Authorization: {YOUR_SANCTUM_TOKEN}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json"
const url = new URL(
    "http://surukori.top/api/googlehandle"
);

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "{YOUR_SANCTUM_TOKEN}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers,
}).then(response => response.json());
Received response:
Request failed with error:


Tip: Check that you're properly connected to the network.
If you're a maintainer of ths API, verify that your API is running and you've enabled CORS.
You can check the Dev Tools console for debugging information.

POST api/additionalinformation

requires authentication

Example request:
curl --request POST \
    "http://surukori.top/api/additionalinformation" \
    --header "Authorization: {YOUR_SANCTUM_TOKEN}" \
    --header "Content-Type: application/json" \
    --header "Accept: application/json" \
    --data "{
    \"formData\": {
        \"gender\": \"male\",
        \"fname\": \"i\",
        \"lname\": \"y\",
        \"password\": \"pBNvYg\",
        \"birthdate_day\": 2,
        \"birthdate_month\": 1,
        \"birthdate_year\": \"2026\"
    },
    \"email\": \"zbailey@example.net\"
}"

const url = new URL(
    "http://surukori.top/api/additionalinformation"
);

const headers = {
    "Authorization": "{YOUR_SANCTUM_TOKEN}",
    "Content-Type": "application/json",
    "Accept": "application/json",
};

let body = {
    "formData": {
        "gender": "male",
        "fname": "i",
        "lname": "y",
        "password": "pBNvYg",
        "birthdate_day": 2,
        "birthdate_month": 1,
        "birthdate_year": "2026"
    },
    "email": "zbailey@example.net"
};

fetch(url, {
    method: "POST",
    headers,
    body: JSON.stringify(body),
}).then(response => response.json());

If you're a maintainer of ths API, verify that your API is running and you've enabled CORS.

Request      

POST api/additionalinformation

Headers

Authorization        

Example: {YOUR_SANCTUM_TOKEN}

Content-Type        

Example: application/json

Accept        

Example: application/json

Body Parameters

formData   object  optional    
gender   string     

Example: male

Must be one of:
  • male
  • female
  • others
fname   string     

Must not be greater than 50 characters. Example: i

lname   string     

Must not be greater than 50 characters. Example: y

password   string     

Must be at least 8 characters. Example: pBNvYg

birthdate_day   integer     

Must be between 1 and 31. Example: 2

birthdate_month   integer     

Must be between 1 and 12. Example: 1

birthdate_year   string     

Must be a valid date in the format Y. Example: 2026

email   string     

Must be a valid email address. Example: zbailey@example.net
